---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Comzip Calculators' privacy policy."
  path="/privacy"
  lang="en"
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="note" style="margin-top:0;">Effective date: July 20, 2026</p>

  <p>
    Comzip Calculators (hereinafter "the Site") takes the protection of users'
    personal information seriously and complies with Korea's Personal Information
    Protection Act and other applicable laws. The following describes how the
    Site handles personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Personal Information Collected and Collection Methods</h2>
  <p>
    The Site does not offer membership registration or login. Values you enter
    into calculators (salary, announced value, date of birth, etc.) are{' '}
    <strong>
      not transmitted to or stored on any server — they are calculated and
      processed entirely within your browser
    </strong>
    . In other words, information you enter while using a calculator is not
    shared with anyone, including the operator.
  </p>
  <p>
    However, the following information may be collected automatically to help
    improve the service.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> — Usage statistics such as pages
      visited, time spent, device and browser type, and approximate location
      (country/city level). Collected via cookies and processed in a form that
      does not identify any specific individual.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Advertising service cookies</strong> — To support site operations,
      third-party advertisements (e.g., Google AdSense) may be displayed. In
      that case, advertising providers may use cookies to serve personalised ads.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Purpose of Collection and Use of Personal Information</h2>
  <p>
    Automatically collected information is used solely for analysing service
    usage, improving content and features, and displaying advertisements. It is
    not used for any other purpose.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Retention Period of Personal Information</h2>
  <p>
    The Site does not independently store or retain personal information.
    Information collected through Google Analytics is handled in accordance with
    Google's data retention policy. For details, please refer to Google's
    Privacy Policy linked below.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Sharing and Processing</h2>
  <p>
    As a rule, the Site does not provide users' personal information to outside
    parties. However, because the Site uses third-party services such as Google
    Analytics and Google AdSense, automatically collected information may be
    transmitted to the respective service providers (e.g., Google) to the extent
    necessary for those services to function.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Advertising Policies</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Installation, Operation, and Opt-Out of Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files that store and periodically retrieve information
    about your visits and usage patterns. You can refuse or delete cookies
    through your web browser settings. Please note that refusing cookies may
    cause some parts of the service to function incorrectly.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Chrome: Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
    <li>Safari: Preferences → Privacy</li>
    <li>Edge: Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can also install the{' '}
    <a
      href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a
    >{' '}
    to block data collection by Google Analytics.
  </p>

  <h2>6. User Rights and How to Exercise Them</h2>
  <p>
    You may contact us at any time using the details below to enquire about how
    your personal information is being processed, or to request access,
    correction, or deletion. Because the Site does not hold member identification
    information, it will help us respond if you specify what information your
    request relates to (for example, a particular visit record) when you get in
    touch.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Privacy Officer</h2>
  <p>
    For enquiries regarding site operations or the handling of personal
    information, please contact us at:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Operator: Comzip Calculators</li>
    <li>Email: comzip@gmail.com</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Notice of Changes</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be amended, supplemented, or revised in response to
    changes in laws, policies, or the service. Any changes will be announced on
    the Site.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
